    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The phenomenon, similar in principle to electron diffraction, whereby a beam of neutrons scattered by the regularly spaced atoms of a solid produces diffraction patterns characteristic of the solid’s crystal structure. Neutron diffraction may be used in place of x-ray crystallography.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
